PROBLEM: Write an algorithm to determine if a number n is happy. Return true if n is a happy number, and false if not.
LANGUAGE:JAVA

SOL:

class Solution {

     public int getNext(int n) {
        int totalSum = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            int d = n % 10;
            n = n / 10;
            totalSum += d * d;
        }
        return totalSum;
    }

    public boolean isHappy(int n) {
        int slowRunner = n;
        int fastRunner = getNext(n);
        while (fastRunner != 1 && slowRunner != fastRunner) {
            slowRunner = getNext(slowRunner);
            fastRunner = getNext(getNext(fastRunner));
        }
        return fastRunner == 1;
    }
}

TEST CASE 1
Input: n = 19
Output: true
Explanation:
12 + 92 = 82
82 + 22 = 68
62 + 82 = 100
12 + 02 + 02 = 1

TEST CASE 2
Input: n = 2
Output: false
